title: Space tech startup True Anomaly set to launch its first satellites
summary: The company’s first two Jackal spacecraft are scheduled to launch aboard SpaceX's upcoming Transporter-10 rideshare

title: Unseenlabs books SpaceX to expand maritime surveillance constellation
summary: French maritime surveillance provider Unseenlabs plans to launch its 12th and 13th nanosatellite no earlier than March, passing the halfway mark for a constellation slated to begin tracking vessels in near real-time in 2025.

title: Launch Roundup: SpaceX launching three Falcon 9 rockets including Crew-8; new launcher to debut from Japan
summary: This week now has four flights scheduled, starting with Crew-8, which is to send a new crew to the International Space Station for a six-month tour of duty after launching from Florida. Starlink 6-41 from Cape Canaveral and Transporter 10 from Vandenberg Space Force Base are also on the docket along with the debut of a new small satellite launcher from Japan.
